<section xml:id="summary-odds-ratio">
  <title>Summary of Inference for Odds Ratio</title>

  <assemblage>
    <title>Odds Ratio Procedures</title>

    <p><alert>Statistic:</alert> <m>\hat{\tau} = [\hat{p}_1/(1-\hat{p}_1)]/[\hat{p}_2/(1-\hat{p}_2)] = (A \times D) / (B \times C)</m></p>
    <p>(typically set up to be larger than one)</p>

    <p><alert>Hypotheses:</alert> H<subscript>0</subscript>: <m>\tau = 1</m>; H<subscript>a</subscript>: <m>\tau</m> &lt;, >, or â‰  1</p>

    <p><alert>p-value:</alert> Fisher's Exact Test</p>
    <p>You can also use simulation (assuming the probabilities of success are equal) or a normal approximation on <m>\ln(\hat{\tau})</m></p>

    <p><alert>Confidence interval for <m>\tau</m>:</alert> exponential of</p>
    <p><me>\ln(\hat{\tau}) \pm z^*\sqrt{\frac{1}{A}+\frac{1}{B}+\frac{1}{C}+\frac{1}{D}}</me></p>

    <p><alert>Technology:</alert></p>
    <p><ul>
      <li>In Two-way Tables applet: Choose Odds Ratio as statistic and check box for 95% CI</li>
      <li>In R: fisher.test(matrix(c(a, c, b, d), nrow=2), alt = )</li>
      <li>In JMP: From the Contingency Analysis hot spot, choose Odds Ratio</li>
    </ul></p>
  </assemblage>

